<remark>
  Notice that in <xref ref="act-log-calc"/> part (g) you were unable to evaluate the logarithm. Given that exponentials and logarithms are inverses, their domain and range are related.  The range of an expnential function is <m>(0,\infty)</m> which becomes the domain of a logarithmic function.  This means that the argument of any logarithmic function must be greater than zero.
</remark>

<activity xml:id="act-log-domain">
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Find the domain of the function <m>\log_3(2x-4)</m>.
    </p>
  </introduction>
  <task>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Set up an inquality that you must solve to find the domain.
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>2x-4 \gt 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </task>
  <task>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Solve the inequality to find the domain. Write your answer in interval notation.
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x \gt 2</m> or <m>(2, \infty)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </task>
</activity>

    

